# Auth & identity (Chaupaal)

## Model (Instagram-style)

- **One Firebase Auth identity** per email **or** phone signup (password and/or Google).
- **Many Chaupaal profiles** under that identity — **no hard profile-create cap** (Instagram: unlimited owned; their “5” is simultaneous device logins of separate credentials, not our profile model).
- App uses **active profile** (`activeProfileId`) for posts, chats, display name, username.
- Account switcher lists all profiles under the signed-in identity.

## Signup / contact

- Signup requires **verified email (Gmail/Google or email+password)** **or** **verified phone** (OTP).
- When a user adds email or phone at any stage, **verify with OTP / Firebase verification before treating it as registered**.
- Phone is for signup and recovery/linking; OTP required when phone is used.

## Username

- Globally unique handle; **one profile per username**.
- Rename allowed; **old username freed immediately** (Rename A).

## Session persistence

- Stay signed in on the device across app restarts (**Firebase Auth local persistence**).
- Clear session **only** on explicit logout (or remote session revoke).
- Soft reset for pre-launch: re-register OK; do not build legacy migration this pass.

## Passwords

- Email + password + Google + forgot-password (email reset).
- Do not invent separate payment/auth stacks per feature.
